#    Marin Atanasov Nikolov)
#
#  Maintained by Marin Atanasov Nikolov (dnaeon/cl-migratum).  52 GH
#  stars.  cl-migratum is a DATABASE SCHEMA MIGRATION system for
#  Common Lisp ‚Äî manages incremental SQL schema migrations against
#  PostgreSQL/SQLite/MySQL databases via either the cl-dbi unified
#  driver or the cl-postgres/cl-rdbms-pgsql direct PostgreSQL driver.
#  Migration files are timestamped SQL up/down pairs with descriptive
#  names; cl-migratum tracks applied vs pending state in a migrations
#  metadata table.  Sister tools: Flyway (Java DB migration, in
#  corpus), Liquibase (Java DB migration, IN CORPUS via _liquibase),
#  Alembic (Python DB migration, IN CORPUS via _alembic), Ecto.Migrate
#  (Elixir), goose (Go DB migration, IN CORPUS).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 4th Common Lisp CLI library ‚Äî Marin
#  Atanasov Nikolov's **clingon** (dnaeon/clingon).  Common Lisp
#  ecosystem now has 4 documented CLI libraries.
#
#  Clingon (dnaeon/clingon) is Marin Atanasov Nikolov's modern Common
#  Lisp CLI library ‚Äî inspired by Go's spf13/cobra and Rust's clap.
#  Supports nested subcommands, typed options with enum/integer/
#  string/boolean/list-of-X/filepath types, env-var fallbacks,
#  pre/post hooks, custom handlers, automatic --help/--version,
#  Zsh/Bash/Fish completion generation.  Used by cl-migratum (DB
#  schema migration), ocicl-templates (CL ASDF distribution
#  templates), Screenshotbot OSS (300 stars screenshot testing),
#  Shop3 (165 stars HTN planner), Red Light Green Light (Anthony
#  Green's policy enforcement), Anthony Green's icl (interactive
#  Common Lisp REPL, 176 stars), CIEL CL utilities, Kiln (CL
#  scripting), Portofino CMS Lisp CLI, LunaNode CLI, ryukinix
#  lisp-chat admin, and most modern Common Lisp CLI tools that
#  want structured subcommand-based design.
#
